# Changelog discipline

- Before **any changelog edit** tied to new product/docs/test work, confirm workflow order: run the **quality gate** in one terminal — [testing-terminal-isolation.mdc](testing-terminal-isolation.mdc) — `yarn testbatch:verify` when product or test sources changed (see [eslint-typescript.mdc](eslint-typescript.mdc)); then Storybook updates/checks for affected **`src/components/**`** UI (**`yarn storybook:run`** / **`yarn storybook:build`** as needed; layout/page Storybook previews do not require Docs/autodocs); then changelog update.
- After **substantive** product or user-visible changes, update [changeLog.md](src/i18n/en-US/documents/changeLog.md) using the existing [package.json](package.json) `version` as the only version source per [fantasia-changelog-en-us skill](../skills/fantasia-changelog-en-us/SKILL.md).
- Immediately before editing changelog content, re-read [package.json](package.json) and use that live `version` value; do not rely on previously cached values.
- When preparing changelog updates, also inspect `.cursor/plans/` for plan files that match the current `package.json.version` to gather release-context notes for what changed.
- **NEVER, EVER, UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES** auto-bump, infer, or mutate any version value in `package.json` or changelog headings.
- **Always** append or edit changelog content under the section that matches the current `package.json.version`, unless the user explicitly asks for a manual version change.
- **Do not** turn the in-app changelog into an internal QA or CI log: **omit** bullets whose only substance is that maintainers re-ran `yarn testbatch:verify`, `yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`, `yarn testbatch:ensure:change`, `yarn lint:eslint`, `yarn lint:typescript`, `yarn lint:stylelint`, `yarn test:unit`, production `yarn quasar:build:electron`, Playwright component runs, E2E runs, Storybook smoke/visual runs, or other verification (“all tests passed”, “pipeline green”). Those belong in commits, PRs, or team notes. The changelog is for **what changed** for users or the shipped product, not **how** it was validated.
- **Omit** any `###` category (`New features`, `Known issues`, `Bugfixes & Optimizations`, etc.) when there is nothing to list — no empty sections and no “none” placeholder bullets.

## Local types extraction rule

- For Vue (`.vue`) and TypeScript (`.ts`) source files, move small file-local interfaces/type aliases into a colocated `<filename>.types.ts` file and import them back.
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
